    "When working on the recipe generation flow, assume a REST API endpoint like /api/generate-recipes that accepts JSON and returns JSON.",
    "Recipe objects should follow a consistent shape: { id, title, ingredients, steps, prepTimeMinutes, difficulty, estimatedCalories, tags } where ingredients and steps are arrays of strings.",
    "Handle loading, error, and empty states explicitly in UI components.",
    "Avoid unnecessary dependencies. Use the built-in Web APIs and React features where possible.",
    "Write small, named helper functions for repetitive logic (e.g., formatting ingredients, capitalizing labels).",
    "Prefer async/await over raw Promise chains.",
    "Validate user input lightly on the client (e.g., ignore empty ingredient strings, trim whitespace).",
    "Use semantic HTML elements where possible (button, form, main, section, header).",
